sub_title: Logistics & Operations Coordinator at Blue Skies
summary:
Hello, 

Welcome to my profile. I am Ivica, 28 year-old young man from Croatia (depends on who you ask but still consider myself young) mag.ing. of logistics and management in the maritime industry and transport. 

During my studies, I was a member of the student council at my Faculty, a member of AIESEC and ESN, a participant in many student projects, case studies, volunteering events, even led my own project - a field trip for my university colleagues to Port of Koper.

I am 3 times Erasmus exchange participant - the first student exchange was in Wismar, Germany while 2nd was in Piraeus/Athens in Greece. 3rd one was an internship in Warsaw, Poland as an assistant forwarder. These ERASMUS exchanges taught me to step out of my comfort zone, adapt to new countries, cultures and mentalities, be more confident, assertive, proactive, met many new people from all over the world and perfected my communication skills.

After my internship, went to the Netherlands on two occasions to gain some experience in logistics/warehousing, saw how warehouse logistics & distribution processes work from the bottom to up and gained valuable experience working in large teams, learnt to be more resourceful, responsible and give my best to whatever I am doing. 

Aspiring to keep learning, developing and growing (personally and professionally) myself further in the field of logistics and supply chain, procurement, demand planning, project management, languages etc.

[{'title': 'Case Study Realizator - City of Rijeka (Rijeka tunnel)', 'date': {'start': {'month': 10, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}, 'end': {'month': 12, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}}, 'description': 'For the third time in a row I participated at the University of Rijeka Foundation case study competition called Realizator. We worked on a case study given by the city of Rijeka on a subject matter - how to turn Rijeka tunnel into an active place of social life in the city of Rijeka?
', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Ivica', 'last_name': 'Pavičić', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Logistics & Operations Coordinator at Blue Skies'}, {'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Andrea', 'last_name': 'Hrelja', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Data Engineer at iOLAP'}]}, {'title': 'Field trip to Port Koper', 'date': {'start': {'month': 11, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}, 'end': {'month': 12, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}}, 'description': "As an unofficial member of the Student Council at my Faculty, I was a project leader on this project. I organized, hired a bus, reserved a date at the port of Koper, coordinated with the president of the Student Council and other members who helped me to execute this project until the end. 42 students out of 49 went on this trip, We had a tour of the port. 

Goal of this project was to give students of the Faculty of Maritime Studies insight and knowledge into their profession, to motivate them to develop their skills and gain some practical experience that we lack after finishing our degree (especially for the students of logistics and technology at our Faculty). 

For myself personally, this was the first time as a project leader, it was very stressful and nerve-wrecking, I saw what kind of choices I don't want to make, learned something about myself and one big lesson for the future, overall very valuable experience that I am grateful for.", 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Ivica', 'last_name': 'Pavičić', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Logistics & Operations Coordinator at Blue Skies'}]}, {'title': 'University of Rijeka Case Study Realizator - Infobip', 'date': {'start': {'month': 11, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}, 'end': {'month': 12, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}}, 'description': 'Infobip case study - How to attract and keep IT engineers in Croatia ', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Ivica', 'last_name': 'Pavičić', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Logistics & Operations Coordinator at Blue Skies'}, {'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Kristian', 'last_name': 'Kirinčić', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Lead Generation Manager | Virtual Assistant | Social Media Manager | Team Leader | Drummer & Mentor | Band Manager | Crypto Investor'}, {'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Augustin', 'last_name': 'Sočković', 'name': None, 'headline': 'SW Developer at SVAM plus'}]}, {'title': 'Theater Play "Mind on a break"', 'date': {'start': {'month': 2, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}, 'end': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}}, 'description': 'I entered in school of acting in Ri Theater Kalvarija as a member of 31st generation. It lasted four months, from February to May and as a result of those 4 months we did our play on 3rd and 4th of June in Kalvarija in front of 150+ people on both days. During that  period we were learning all sorts of acting techniques, exercises, improvisation...that we later used in a Jerry Springer type of play in which we had to play our characters without breaking out of them. After that, next step was to make play of our own (there were 14 of us at the end including me). Every single one of us had to come up with their own character to play, we were playing lunatics who thought they were living in a building. To them it was a perfect little world. In fact they were in a asylum run by 3 doctors and a warden who were skillfully deceiving them that they are normal. On the other hand lunatics were thinking that doctors are the ones who are crazy and they actually managed to escape with a mission to seek help for them. After they escaped they witnessed murder, rape and later came back to the asylum(their building) concluding that the outside world is insane and they are better off as they were before.
I played Vicko Gilmeršić, lunatic who was into James Bond, espionage type of stuff. He was always talking in third person, he was a paranoid and overly suspicious of everyone, occasionally had anger outbursts and he was the leader of the escape from asylum...', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Ivica', 'last_name': 'Pavičić', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Logistics & Operations Coordinator at Blue Skies'}, {'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Dolores', 'last_name': 'Rajnović', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Senior Project Manager at Mack Project Engineering Group'}]}, {'title': 'Career Booster Rijeka', 'date': {'start': {'month': 2, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}, 'end': {'month': 3, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}}, 'description': 'Career Booster is a unique concept  that enables students and young people to acquire knowledge and skills needed for faster and easier transition to the business world.
